      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Oct 2 article in Business Day about marketing of violent video games to children</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Monday about the marketing of violent video games to children misstated the legal action that the Federal Trade Commission might take in such cases. Jodie Z. Bernstein, director of the commission's bureau of consumer protection, said the agency was exploring civil complaints over deceptive or unfair trade practices by game makers or other entertainment companies that market adult content to children. She did not say criminal charges might apply.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
